<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hideous" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hideous,</orth> (dissyll.; trisyll. in <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 4, 34</bibl>) frightful, shocking, horrible: <bibl n="shak. luc 973" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 973</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. son 5.6" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 5, 6</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.12.2" default="NO" valid="yes">12, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wiv 4.4.34" default="NO" valid="yes">Wiv. IV, 4, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mm 1.4.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 4, 63</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.52" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 52</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 1.5.221" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 5, 221</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.34" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 2, 34</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.2.266" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 2, 266</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.4.22" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 4, 22</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 2.3.35" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B II, 3, 35</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 3h6 5.6.46" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C V, 6, 46</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 1.4.60" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 4, 60</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.90" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 90</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.3.50" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 3, 50</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jc 2.1.65" default="NO" valid="yes">Caes. II, 1, 65</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.87" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 87</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 1.4.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 4, 54</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ham 2.2.498" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 498</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.4.282" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 4, 282</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 3.3.108" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. III, 3, 108</bibl>. <cit><quote>drive the gentleman into a most h. opinion of his rage,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.212" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 212</bibl></cit> (i. e. into an opinion of the extreme hideousness of his rage). <cit><quote>check this h. rashness,</quote> <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.153" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 153</bibl></cit> (shocking, in a moral sense).
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>